.TH "ciclog" "1" "2026\-07\-17" "ciclog 1.0.5" "CIC Commands Manual"
.SH NAME
ciclog \(en Log formatting and handling for CIC
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
ciclog [\f[I]LEVEL\f[R]] [\f[I]MESSAGE\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[B]ciclog\f[R] is a logging tool that prepends
\f[CR]${EPOCHREALTIME}\f[R] and \f[CR]${FUNCNAME[1]}\f[R] to
\f[I]LEVEL\f[R] and \f[I]MESSAGE\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]ciclog\f[R] also defines some common exit codes for custom cic
programs, like \f[CR]cicdaemon\f[R].
.PD 0
.P
.PD
See \f[B]EXIT STATUS\f[R] for more information.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Unless defined otherwise here, or in another program, \f[B]CIC\f[R]
programs will use the same exit code conventions as
\f[B]sysexits.h\f[R](3head), including the exit status variables.
.TP
\f[B]0\f[R], \f[B]EX_OK\f[R]
\f[CR]successful termination\f[R]
.TP
